    "summary": "Finance Professional with broad experience in administration, accounting and financial management. Due to my consultancy background I developed experience in a wide variety of businesses, from Real Estate Management to IT but also at a hospital. Furthermore I also have experience at international NGO's.\n\nSpecialties: \n\u2022\tFinancial Management\nAs a career professional from corporate and non-profit sectors, I have more than 10 years experience in Finance Management in The Netherlands, Pakistan, Timor Leste, Liberia and Jordan. Combined with my academic qualifications, I have advanced skills in the core aspects of Financial management: financial planning, monitoring & control, budget deviation analysis and governance (accountability & oversight). \n\u2022\tProject Grant Management\nThroughout my work for NGOs in Pakistan, Timor-Leste and Liberia, I have gained considerable experience in regards to the requirements of donors, specifically DFID, EU, Global Fund, GIZ, Caritas International, USAID, TearFund, Dutch and Norwegian Governments.\n\u2022\tCapacity Development/Training & Coaching\nI have been training and coaching colleagues since I became a finance consultant in 2005, as it is important that my skills are transferred to new staff.  For the non-profit (development) sector, I have coached the acting Finance Manager of Equip Liberia and the Country Director, the Country Representative and the Finance Officer of Progressio Timor-Leste. At Progressio, I also gave Financial Management training to the Finance Officers and their Directors of 10 different local NGOs. My teamwork skills have evolved to reflect the cultural diversity where I have worked in. \n\u2022\tFinance IT Skills \nI have advance IT skills on Finance-related software like: Quickbooks, SAP \u2013 FICO, Oracle, BAAN, J.D. Edwards, Masterpiece, FIS 2000, Real Estate Management System (REMS), Business Objects, TM1 and the Microsoft Office products.",
